titles.title: A bill to designate the Federal building in Jacksonville, Florida, as the "Charles E. Bennett Federal Building".

action.text: Sponsor introductory remarks on measure. (CR S9720)
Read twice and referred to the Committee on Governmental Affairs.
Senate Committee on Governmental Affairs discharged by Unanimous Consent.
Referred to the Committee on Environment and Public Works.

committee.name: Committee on Environment and Public Works

calendar.text: Committee on Environment and Public Works. Ordered to be reported without amendment favorably.

action.text: Committee on Environment and Public Works. Reported to Senate by Senator Baucus without amendment. Without written report.

calendar.text: Placed on Senate Legislative Calendar under General Orders. Calendar No. 198.

action.text: Senate passed companion measure H.R. 2431 in lieu of this measure by Voice Vote.
Indefinitely postponed by Senate by Unanimous Consent.

bill.summary: 7/28/1993--Introduced. Designates the Federal building at 400 Bay Street, Jacksonville, Florida, (or any building built to replace it) as the Charles E. Bennett Federal Building.
